quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  3,141,and so that Allah can purge those who have iman and wipe out the kafirun
  3,142,Or did you imagine that you were going to enter the Garden without Allah knowing those among you who had struggled and knowing the steadfast
  3,143,You were longing for death before you met it. Now you have seen it with your own eyes
  3,144,"Muhammad is only a Messenger and he has been preceded by other Messengers. If he were to die or be killed, would you turn on your heels? Those who turn on their heels do not harm Allah in any way. Allah will recompense the thankful"
  3,145,"No self can die except with Allah´s permission, at a predetermined time. If anyone desires the reward in this world, We will give him some of it. If anyone desires the reward in the Next World, We will give him some of it. We will recompense the thankful"
  3,146,"Many a Prophet has been killed, when there were many thousands with him! They did not give up in the face of what assailed them in the Way of Allah, nor did they weaken, nor did they yield. Allah loves the steadfast"
  3,147,"All they said was, ´Our Lord, forgive us our wrong actions and any excesses we went to in what we did and make our feet firm and help us against these kafir people.´"
  3,148,So Allah gave them the reward in this world and the best reward in the Next World. Allah loves good-doers